because of it. That's you, isn't it?

252
00:19:13,169 --> 00:19:15,589
No, that's not it.

253
00:19:15,729 --> 00:19:19,809
That's terrible. Want me to
talk to Chika for you?

254
00:19:20,069 --> 00:19:21,969
No! What are you saying?

255
00:19:22,509 --> 00:19:30,036
But it's important. I feel bad for you.
That stuff can wait till you're our age.

256
00:19:30,409 --> 00:19:34,469
I don't wanna hear this.
Don't you dare say anything to Chika.

257
00:19:34,769 --> 00:19:37,210
Why don't you get a divorce?

258
00:19:38,329 --> 00:19:40,769
Huh? Where'd that come from?

259
00:19:41,229 --> 00:19:44,279
I can still look after you if it's just you.

260
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:46,629
It must be hard
being mistreated.

261
00:19:46,722 --> 00:19:49,709
Chika would be better
off without you too.

262
00:19:50,669 --> 00:19:57,510
Think about her feelings too. Attachment
never ends well. Declutter people too.

263
00:19:57,689 --> 00:20:00,449
Enough, Mom. You're not making sense.
I'm hanging up.

264
00:20:36,239 --> 00:20:39,230
Hey, do you have a minute?

265
00:20:40,439 --> 00:20:43,290
Ugh. I'm trying to sleep.

266
00:20:45,139 --> 00:20:46,716
Grandma...

267
00:20:47,735 --> 00:20:49,763
She passed away.

268
00:20:51,299 --> 00:20:52,499
When?

269
00:20:54,025 --> 00:20:55,305
This afternoon.

270
00:20:57,099 --> 00:20:58,530
I see.

271
00:20:59,799 --> 00:21:01,403
So there'll be a funeral.

272
00:21:01,999 --> 00:21:03,510
Yeah.

273
00:21:05,508 --> 00:21:07,422
What should we do?

274
00:21:11,759 --> 00:21:15,783
Would I really have to go to the funeral?

275
00:21:16,379 --> 00:21:17,579
What?

276
00:21:20,739 --> 00:21:27,056
I mean, it's your grandma.
I only met her once or twice.

277
00:21:28,259 --> 00:21:30,896
It's hard for me to take off work.

278
00:21:31,949 --> 00:21:37,869
I've left early a lot this month for Taro's
therapy and school counselor meetings.

279
00:21:38,119 --> 00:21:39,903
And I also had your work.

280
00:21:42,136 --> 00:21:46,239
But still, she's family.

281
00:21:47,559 --> 00:21:49,263
Well, yeah, but...

282
00:21:51,669 --> 00:21:53,210
Whatever, fine.

283
00:21:54,629 --> 00:21:56,383
I'll go, okay?

284
00:21:57,469 --> 00:22:00,230
I really can't stand your family.

285
00:22:00,709 --> 00:22:01,909
Your mother.

286
00:22:06,469 --> 00:22:13,130
I felt like Chika was slowly
decluttering me and my family from her life.

287
00:22:15,070 --> 00:22:16,083
Next Episode Preview

288
00:22:16,123 --> 00:22:17,809
This family is seriously messed up.

289
00:22:17,869 --> 00:22:19,069
Let go!

290
00:22:19,194 --> 00:22:21,649
What if she actually leaves me?!

291
00:22:21,689 --> 00:22:24,869
Who's gonna support me then?!

292
00:22:25,649 --> 00:22:27,435
We need to talk tonight.
